> This post is an intuitive derivation of the Maxwell--Boltzmann, Fermi--Dirac, Bose--Einstein statistics followed by classical, Fermionic, and Bosonic particles, respectively.

The quantum statistics of particles describe the probability of a particle occupying a state of a specified energy $$E$$ at thermal equilibrium. Specifically, we consider the quantum statistics of classical, Fermionic, and Bosonic particles.

The discussions of this post follows directly from Chapter 11-3 of "Quantum Physics of Atoms, Molecules, Solids, Nuclei, and Particles" by Robert Eisberg and Robert Resnick.


